messages.message:
What python version are people dev in with the m1 chipset? i am having a hard time getting cryptography to build properly. Tried 3.9.13 and 3.10.5. Openssl is installed. Running pyenv with virtualenv and no luck on this arm chipset. Tried this as well `env LDFLAGS="-L$(brew --prefix openssl)/lib" CFLAGS="-I$(brew --prefix openssl)/include" pip install -r requirements.txt`
```build/temp.macosx-12.2-arm64-cpython-39/_openssl.c:575:10: fatal error: 'openssl/opensslv.h' file not found
      #include <openssl/opensslv.h>
ERROR: Failed building wheel for cryptography```
Figured it out `cryptography==3.3.2` must have a bug in m1 mac. Took the latest and it compiles now
